title: A Shop ZERO/POINT From Back A Site
description: This is a useful low-risk ZERO/POINT to suppress / scan the inside of A Hall.

title: Middle Of A Pyramids FRAG/MENT To Delay Spike Plant
description: This is a great FRAG/MENT to delay the Attackers from planting the Spike in the center of the A Pyramids, or at least do damage to them if they attempt to plant the Spike there while potentially forcing them to plant the Spike elsewhere.

title: A Site Execute ZERO/POINT From Tree
description: Use this simple, but effective knife lineup that allows you to scale site with it. A great knife to use when planning on using other utility while you execute the site.

title: Fast Arcade Knife for Information
description: Use this lineup at the start of the round to gain information on Defenders, and deny control more effectively towards Arcade.

title: B Tree To B Tower Support / Info ZERO/POINT
description: Here's a great support ZERO/POINT lineup for B Tower from B Tree. Unless you have a reason to; try to time the ZERO/POINT so that you gather information with it, and make it more difficult for enemy players in B Tower to help their teammates defend B as your team pushes into Site.

title: A Dish ZERO/POINT From Attacker Bridge
description: Here's a simple, but effective early round ZERO/POINT for A Dish from Attacker Bridge.

title: A Hall To A Main ZERO/POINT
description: Here's a simple, but effective ZERO/POINT for A Main from A Hall.

title: Back B Bench To B Tower ZERO/POINT
description: Here's a great ZERO/POINT lineup from B Bench for B Tower. This ZERO/POINT suppresses the entirety of B Tower, and is not able to be broken by Defenders who have pushed into Arcade.

title: How to Fight Tree With FLASH/DRIVE
description: Use this simple, but effective flash lineup to peek Tree. This flash forces Attackers to get full blinded, or turn away, letting you shoot them for free.

title: Start Round Dish ZERO/POINT for Info
description: Throw this knife at the start of the round to detect any Attackers looking to take Dish control.

title: A Main Roof FLASH/DRIVE Lineup
description: Enable yourself, or your teammates, with this incredibly powerful flash lineup. This flash does not blind you if you are peeking the Attackers contesting A Main.

title: How to Contest A Main Through Sands With FLASH/DRIVE
description: Here's a standard, but strong way to contest A Main with KAY/O. Your teammate playing deep A Main will be able to fight with you, as the flash does not blind them when peeking when thrown as shown in the video. There is no specific lineup with the flash, just pop and fight as Attackers will look in your direction as they hear the door open.

title: Early Round ZERO/POINT For A Hall / Attacker Bridge
description: Here's a great early round ZERO/POINT for A Hall / Attacker Bridge, that is very difficult for Attackers in and around A Hall / Attacker Bridge to destroy.

title: Early Round Pop Flash For B Tree From B Main
description: Here's a quick early round pop flash for B Tree from B Main, that you can swing with to try to get a pick on players aggressively pushing into B Tree. However, when swinging out to pick off flashed players - avoid peeking out far enough that players playing the anti-flash angles in Attacker Spawn can see you.

title: B Main To B Tree ZERO/POINT
description: Here's a simple, but effective ZERO/POINT for B Tree from B Main / B Site. The ZERO/POINT can be wallbanged and destroyed by enemies in B Tree, so try to throw it at different spots on the side of the tall box in B Tree as showcased on-screen.

title: How to Chain Utility A Main to A Site FLASH/DRIVE
description: Here's one way to perform an execute on the A Site from the beginning of spawn, but you don't need to throw utility as quick as this. The idea is to take A Main with your flash, and then execute the site with your knife.

title: A Side Spawn Barrier to A/Mid Connector ZERO/POINT
description: Here's a simple, but effective early round ZERO/POINT from the A Spawn Barrier to the A/Mid Connector.

title: Early Round A Main ZERO/POINT from A Site
description: Here's a great way to scan players toward the A Side Attacker Spawn Barrier from A Site at the beginning of the round.

title: Early Round B Main ZERO/POINT for B Ramp
description: Here's a simple, but effective way to check for players pushing through B Ramp into B Main from the B Attacker Spawn Barrier.

title: Quick C Link to C Main FLASH/DRIVE to Support C Hold / Retake
description: Use this FLASH/DRIVE when rotating to C to catch enemy players pushing through C Main off guard and support your team.

title: C Main ZERO/POINT from C Lobby Spawn Barrier
description: Use this ZERO/POINT lineup from the C Lobby spawn barrier to check for Defenders peeking / pushing into C Main from C Site.

title: Early Round A Main ZERO/POINT from A Lobby
description: Here's a simple, but effective early round ZERO/POINT for A Main from A Lobby.

title: Early Round ZERO/POINT + FLASH/POINT for B Site
description: Use this simple early round ZERO/POINT + FLASH/POINT setup to aggressively take space on B Site.

title: Aggressive C Main FLASH/DRIVE from C Lobby
description: Use this aggressive FLASH/DRIVE either to make it more difficult for enemy players to take space in C Main at the beginning of the round, or to push into C Main at any stage of the round.

title: Early Round A Main FLASH/DRIVE to Contest Space
description: Use this early round A Main Flash Lineup to contest space in A Main with your teammates.

title: Early Round A Lobby ZERO/POINT from B Main
description: Use this ZERO/POINT lineup from B Main to scan for enemy players in A Lobby at the start of the round.

title: Early Round A Lobby ZERO/POINT from A Main
description: Here's a simple, but effective early round ZERO/POINT for A Lobby from the Defender A Main Spawn Barrier.

title: A Short Trademark + Rendezvous Setup
description: Here's a simple, but effective Trademark + Rendezvous setup for A Lobby and A Short.

title: C Site Rendezvous for Top of C Default
description: Here's a simple, but effective Rendezvous for Top of C Default.

title: B Site Rendezvous + Trademark Setup
description: Here's a simple, but effective B Site Rendezvous + Trademark Setup.

title: Catwalk Lurk Rendezvous + Trademark
description: Use this Rendezvous + Trademark lurk setup that can allow you to lurk up Catwalk, and catch enemy players off guard inside of A Tree. Be sure to ask your teammates to use smokes and other utility to limit what enemy players can do in areas in Mid that the Defenders may spot you from, and attempt to control the enemy team's information in Mid.

title: Bottom Mid Lurk Rendezvous to Watch Rotations
description: Roughly follow this pathing, and use this Rendezvous to catch players rotating through Mid Market off guard. If no enemy players rotate through this area of the map, you may even be able to flank the enemy team later in the round, after your team has taken control of one of the Sites. Be sure to ask your teammates to use smokes and other utility to limit what enemy players can do in areas in Mid that the Defenders may spot you from, and attempt to control the enemy team's information in Mid.

title: B Main Rendezvous Variations
description: Use these two Rendezvous Variations to allow you to play inside of B Main the way that you want to within the round.

title: Early Round Aggressive Bottom Mid Rendezvous
description: Here's a simple but effective early round Bottom Mid Rendezvous.

title: Aggressive Catwalk Rendezvous
description: Here's a simple, but effective aggressive Catwalk Rendezvous.

title: Aggressive Mid Tube Rendezvous from Kitchen
description: Here's a simple, but effective aggressive Mid Tube Rendezvous from Kitchen.

title: A Screen Rendezvous for Mid A Site
description: Here's a simple, but effective A Screens Rendezvous for Mid A Site.

title: B Tower Rendezvous to Lock Down B Arcade
description: Use this post plant setup after your team has taken control of B Site and B Tower to help lock down Arcade, and create options for how you can play from inside of Arcade to help your team hold down B Site.

title: Versatile A Rope Rendezvous
description: This A Rope Rendezvous allows you to hold a passive angle on enemy players pushing through A Main into A Rope, hold an angle on A Drop, or challenge enemy players as they push out of A Main onto Site, depending on what's needed within the round.

title: Aggressive Early Round B Main Rendezvous + Trademark Setup
description: Use this early round B Main Rendezvous + Trademark setup to peek into B Main, challenge an enemy player, and then teleport out with utility set up to stall enemy players as they attempt to push into B Site through B Main.

title: Early Round B Arcade + Tunnel Rendezvous
description: This Rendezvous for Arcade allows you to play in many different ways in and around B Site, Arcade, and Tunnel.

title: A Main Rendezvous for Execute or Post Plant
description: This Rendezvous can be used when pushing aggressively into A Site, or for post plant on the side of A.
